#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn17.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn17.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 17 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 17 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthavagga "
msgstr "4. The Fourth Chapter "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 35. Acirapakkantasutta → attavadhasuttaṃ (bj) | pakkanta (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn17.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Acirapakkantasutta "
msgstr "35. Shortly After He Left "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.241, sc1
msgctxt "sn17.35:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate acirapakkante devadatte. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak Mountain, not long after Devadatta had left. "

msgctxt "sn17.35:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā devadattaṃ ārabbha bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha spoke to the mendicants about Devadatta: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.35:1.3"
msgid "“attavadhāya, bhikkhave, devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr "“Possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn17.35:2.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kadalī attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti; "
msgstr "It’s like a banana tree … "

msgctxt "sn17.35:2.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn17.35:3.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, veḷu attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti; "
msgstr "or a bamboo … "

msgctxt "sn17.35:3.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr " "

#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn17.35:4.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷo attavadhāya phalaṃ deti, parābhavāya phalaṃ deti; "
msgstr "or a reed, all of which bear fruit to their own ruin and downfall … "

msgctxt "sn17.35:4.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn17.35:5.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, assatarī attavadhāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti, parābhavāya gabbhaṃ gaṇhāti; "
msgstr "It’s like a mule, which becomes pregnant to its own ruin and downfall. "

msgctxt "sn17.35:5.2"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, attavadhāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi, parābhavāya devadattassa lābhasakkārasiloko udapādi. "
msgstr "In the same way, possessions, honor, and popularity came to Devadatta for his own ruin and downfall. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn17.35:5.3"
msgid "Evaṃ dāruṇo kho, bhikkhave, lābhasakkārasiloko. "
msgstr "So brutal are possessions, honor, and popularity. …” "

msgctxt "sn17.35:5.4"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn17.35:6.1"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā. "
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said. "

msgctxt "sn17.35:6.2"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā: "
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.1"
msgid "“Phalaṃ ve kadaliṃ hanti, "
msgstr "“The banana tree is destroyed by its own fruit, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.2"
msgid "phalaṃ veḷuṃ phalaṃ naḷaṃ; "
msgstr "as are the bamboo and the reed. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.3"
msgid "Sakkāro kāpurisaṃ hanti, "
msgstr "Honor destroys a sinner, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.4"
msgid "gabbho assatariṃ yathā”ti. "
msgstr "as pregnancy destroys a mule.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn17.35:7.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
